p42.text:
(1) An applicant for a driving licence must demonstrate knowledge, skills, and behaviour, including specific requirements for individual vehicle groups, during the practical driving examination. The practical driving examination is divided into two parts. An applicant for a driving licence who fails to demonstrate basic knowledge in each of the two parts of the examination shall be graded as „failed“. The examination commissioner shall make a written record of the course of the practical driving examination. The examination record may also be kept in electronic form.

(2) If an applicant for a driving licence for group AM, A1, A2, or A fails to demonstrate basic knowledge in the first part of the examination, they shall be graded as „failed“ and may not continue to the second part of the examination. If an applicant for a driving licence for group AM, A1, A2, or A fails to demonstrate basic knowledge in the second part of the examination, they shall be graded as „failed“ and the repeated examination shall be conducted only to the extent of the second part of the examination.

(3) In the first part of the examination, the applicant for a driving licence shall demonstrate, in particular:

- a) basic knowledge and skills of vehicle preparation procedures before use;

- b) starting off with varying degrees of difficulty;

- c) stopping the vehicle;

- d) reversing and turning while reversing;

- e) entering and exiting a confined space;

- f) parallel, diagonal, and perpendicular parking of the vehicle;

- g) stopping and starting on an incline;

- h) driving the vehicle at low speed, not exceeding 30 km.h^-1.

(4) In the second part of the examination, the applicant for a driving licence shall demonstrate, in particular, knowledge of:

- a) safe driving of a vehicle with varying traffic intensity on roads;

- b) driving a vehicle on different types of roads;

- c) driving a vehicle at an intersection controlled by traffic lights;

- d) driving a vehicle in an area with public transport and sufficient pedestrian movement with marked pedestrian crossings;

- e) driving a vehicle outside built-up areas and, in the case of large cities, at least on a multi-lane road where a speed higher than 50 km.h^-1 is permitted;

- f) controlling the vehicle at higher speeds and in various manoeuvring situations;

- g) quick and safe decision-making in a traffic situation while driving a vehicle;

- h) correct reaction to an emerging traffic situation.

(5) The condition stipulated in paragraph 4 letter c) may be waived if the applicant completed training at a driving school operator's establishment located in a district where there is no intersection controlled by traffic lights.

(6) The list of individual knowledge, skills, and behaviour, and details of examination requirements, including the particulars of the examination record and the method of its keeping, shall be stipulated by the implementing regulation.

p51.text:
(1) The training centre operator is obliged to:

- a) provide instruction and training according to the instruction and training plan;

- b) ensure the provision of instruction and training by professionally qualified persons;

- c) ensure the provision of instruction and training by means of training vehicles according to § 9 and 10;

- d) for the entire period of its operation, have the right to use non-residential premises and equipment necessary for providing instruction and have these premises and equipment available at all times;

- e) for the entire period of its operation, have the right to use training vehicles necessary for providing training and have these vehicles available at all times;

- f) proceed in accordance with the control system for monitoring the compliance of instruction and training provision with the instruction and training plan;

- g) keep records of completed instruction and training, including a list of participants; and

- h) send, no later than 5 working days before the commencement of instruction or training within the scope of initial and regular training, a list of registered participants, as well as the place, date, and time of commencement of instruction or training, to the regional authority competent according to its registered office, and within the scope of initial training, a list of registered participants, as well as the place, date, and time of commencement of instruction or training, also to the municipal authority of a municipality with extended powers competent according to the location of the establishment where the instruction or training takes place; changes to the list of registered participants may be delivered to the regional authority or the municipal authority of a municipality with extended powers no later than 1 working day before the training takes place;

- i) send, no later than 10 working days from the date on which the regular driver training was completed, to the municipal authority of a municipality with extended powers competent to decide on the driver's professional competence, a list of participants in the regular training.

(2) The training centre operator is obliged to notify the regional authority of changes in data relevant for the granting of accreditation and to submit documents thereof within 15 days from the date on which they occurred.

(3) The training centre operator is obliged to issue without undue delay to a driver who has completed instruction and training at this centre a certificate of the scope and content of the completed instruction and training and the date of completion of the instruction and training.

(4) The training centre operator is obliged to recognise instruction and training to the extent specified in the certificate according to the previous paragraph, which the driver underwent with another training centre operator. For initial training, the training centre operator shall recognise instruction and training according to the first sentence only if no more than 3 months have passed since the completion of the previous instruction and training.

(5) The model of the certificate of completed instruction and training and the date of completion of instruction and training at the training centre shall be stipulated by an implementing legal regulation.

sprilohac2kzakonu.text:
Types of training vehicles for instruction, training, and examination of professional competence to drive motor vehicles and technical requirements for training vehicles

Practical vehicle driving training and the practical driving test shall be conducted on a vehicle classified in the relevant vehicle group, unless otherwise stipulated below, namely:

- a) for group AM, on a moped with an internal combustion engine capacity not exceeding 50 cm^3 and a design speed not exceeding 45 km.h^-1, or on a motorcycle with an internal combustion engine capacity not exceeding 125 cm^3, provided that the driving speed during driving training and practical driving during the practical driving test must not exceed 45 km.h^-1; on a moped with more than 2 wheels, a maximum of 4 hours of training may be conducted;

- b) for group A1, on a motorcycle without a sidecar, with a power output not exceeding 11 kW, a design speed of at least 90 km.h^-1, a power-to-weight ratio not exceeding 0.1 kW/kg, and if it is an internal combustion engine motorcycle, with a cylinder capacity of at least 115 cm^3; for an electric motor, furthermore, with a power-to-weight ratio of at least 0.08 kW/kg;

- c) for group A2, on a motorcycle without a sidecar, with a power output of at least 20 kW but not exceeding 35 kW, a power-to-weight ratio not exceeding 0.2 kW/kg, and if it is an internal combustion engine motorcycle, with a cylinder capacity of at least 250 cm^3; for an electric motor, furthermore, with a power-to-weight ratio of at least 0.15 kW/kg;

- d) for group A, on a motorcycle without a sidecar, with a power output of at least 50 kW and an unladen mass of at least 175 kg, with a cylinder capacity of at least 595 cm^3 for an internal combustion engine and a power-to-weight ratio of at least 0.25 kW/kg for an electric motor;

- e) for group B1, with a motor quadricycle with a design speed of at least 60 km.h^-1;

- f) for group B, with a four-wheeled motor vehicle with a design speed of at least 100 km.h^-1, or, if it concerns training according to § 19 letter b) point 3 or an examination according to § 45b paragraph 3, with a vehicle combination whose maximum authorised mass exceeds 3,500 kg but does not exceed 4,250 kg, composed of such a motor vehicle and a trailer with a maximum authorised mass exceeding 750 kg;

- g) for group B+E, with a vehicle combination whose maximum authorised mass exceeds 3,500 kg, consisting of a motor vehicle specified in letter f) and a trailer with a maximum authorised mass of at least 1,000 kg and a design speed of at least 100 km.h^-1; the trailer must be an enclosed box body with a width and height corresponding at least to the width and height of the motor vehicle, formed by an enclosed separate box or a load area with a tarpaulin on a built-in structure; the enclosed box body may be narrower than the motor vehicle if rearward visibility is possible only by using the external rear-view mirrors of the motor vehicle. During the practical driving test, the actual mass of the trailer must be at least 800 kg;

- h) for group C1, with a motor vehicle with a maximum authorised mass exceeding 5,000 kg, a length of at least 5 m, and a design speed of at least 80 km.h^-1; the vehicle body must be an enclosed box body, which is at least as wide and high as the cab, formed by an enclosed or load area with a tarpaulin on a built-in structure, which does not allow the driver to see behind the vehicle other than through the side rear-view mirrors; the motor vehicle must be equipped with an anti-lock braking system and a recording device according to directly applicable European Union regulation^11);

- i) for group C1+E, with a vehicle combination consisting of a motor vehicle specified in letter h) and a trailer with a maximum authorised mass of at least 1,250 kg and a design speed of at least 80 km.h^-1; the trailer must be an enclosed box body with a width and height corresponding at least to the width and height of the motor vehicle, formed by an enclosed separate box or a load area with a tarpaulin on a built-in structure; the enclosed box body may be narrower than the motor vehicle if rearward visibility is possible only by using the external rear-view mirrors of the motor vehicle; the length of such a vehicle combination must be at least 8 m. During the practical driving test, the actual mass of the trailer must be at least 800 kg;

- j) for group C, with a motor vehicle with a maximum authorised mass of at least 12,000 kg, a length of at least 8 m, a width of at least 2.4 m, and a design speed of at least 80 km.h^-1; the vehicle body must be an enclosed box body, which is at least as wide and high as the cab, formed by an enclosed or load area with a tarpaulin on a built-in structure, which does not allow the driver to see behind the vehicle other than through the side rear-view mirrors; the motor vehicle must be equipped with an anti-lock braking system and a recording device according to directly applicable European Union regulation^11) and a gearbox allowing manual gear selection. During the practical driving test, the actual mass of the vehicle must be at least 10,000 kg;

- k) for group C+E, with a vehicle combination consisting either of a motor vehicle specified in letter j) and a trailer, or a tractor unit with a semi-trailer, whereby the maximum authorised mass of the vehicle combination is at least 20,000 kg, the length of the vehicle combination is at least 14 m, the length of the trailer must be at least 7.5 m, the width of the vehicle combination is at least 2.4 m, and the design speed is at least 80 km.h^-1; the trailer, or semi-trailer, must be an enclosed box body with a width and height corresponding at least to the width and height of the motor vehicle cab, formed by an enclosed separate box or a load area with a tarpaulin on a built-in structure. The tractor unit must be equipped with an anti-lock braking system, a gearbox allowing manual gear selection, and a recording device according to directly applicable European Union regulation^11). During the practical driving test, the actual mass of the vehicle combination must be at least 15,000 kg;

- l) for group D1, with a motor vehicle whose maximum authorised mass is at least 4,000 kg, length is at least 5 m, and design speed is at least 80 km.h^-1; the motor vehicle must be equipped with an anti-lock braking system and a recording device according to directly applicable European Union regulation^11);

- m) for group D1+E, with a vehicle combination consisting of a motor vehicle specified in letter l) and a trailer with a maximum authorised mass of at least 1,250 kg and a design speed of at least 80 km.h^-1; the trailer must be an enclosed box body with a width of at least 2 m and a height of at least 2 m, formed by an enclosed separate box or a load area with a tarpaulin on a built-in structure. During the practical driving test, the actual mass of the vehicle must be at least 800 kg;

- n) for group D, with a motor vehicle with a length of at least 10 m, a width of at least 2.4 m, and a design speed of at least 80 km.h^-1; the motor vehicle must be equipped with an anti-lock braking system and a recording device according to directly applicable European Union regulation^11);

- o) for group D+E, with a vehicle combination consisting of a motor vehicle specified in letter n) and a trailer with a maximum authorised mass of at least 1,250 kg, a width of at least 2.4 m, and a design speed of at least 80 km.h^-1; the trailer must be an enclosed box body with a width of at least 2 m and a height of at least 2 m, formed by an enclosed separate box or a load area with a tarpaulin on a built-in structure. During the practical driving test, the actual mass of the trailer must be at least 800 kg;

- p) for group T, with a self-propelled agricultural or forestry tractor with at least two axles, to which a trailer with a total mass of at least 3,500 kg is attached and loaded to at least 50% of its payload. During practical driving training for group T vehicles, half of the training conducted on a driving range or other training area with the exclusion of other vehicle traffic may be carried out without a trailer.

