Classification of driving simulators and scope of permitted training

Depending on their technical design and degree of development, for the purposes of this Act, the following constitute:

- a) the first group: driving simulators with active forward view, simulation of basic driving characteristics, vehicle sounds, which allow for the practice of basic driving maneuvers;

30% of the 1st stage of training may be replaced by a driving simulator,

- b) the second group: computer-controlled driving simulators meeting the conditions of the first group, which further simulate driving on roads with one lane, horizontal and vertical traffic signs, and driving in difficult lighting conditions;

40% of the 1st stage of training, 10% of the 2nd stage of training, and 5% of the 3rd stage of training may be replaced by a driving simulator,

- c) the third group: driving simulators meeting the conditions of the second group, which further allow for the practice of driving forward and backward on roads with multiple lanes in open country and in a city in light traffic with simple traffic interactions in various lighting regimes, and allow for the practice of risky situations;

40% of the 1st stage of training, 10% of the 2nd stage of training, and 10% of the 3rd stage of training, including the practice of correct conduct in individual risky situations, may be replaced by a driving simulator,

- d) the fourth group: driving simulators meeting the conditions of the third group, which are further equipped with a panoramic forward view, rear views, a movable base, and allow for the practice of driving in full traffic under various climatic conditions;

50% of the 1st stage of training, 30% of the 2nd stage of training, and 15% of the 3rd stage of training, including the practice of correct conduct in individual risky situations, may be replaced by a driving simulator.

If the number of hours obtained by calculation is not an integer, it shall be rounded up to the nearest whole hour.
